import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=50, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('X-coordinate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x-coordinates in the terrain?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    terrain_types = data['name'].value_counts()
    terrain_types.plot(kind='bar', color=['green', 'brown'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of terrain types in the game?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Terrain Type')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
